25footlong pieces of canvas the saudis asked the americans not 
to step there because that is where they face mecca and pray five 
times daily 
how do the two tents communicate 
a 26yearold saudi sergeant had this answer delivered through 
an interpreter 
some of us speak a little english or we use arabic but 
mostly its sign language 
and what do they talk about 
whatever comes to mind the sergeant said 
often the talk is about the heat 
the saudi sergeant sweat running down his face into a thick 
black beard said of his american counterparts god willing they 
will get used to the heat soon 
his advice to the yanks 
keep the flaps of your tent open 
