<TEXT>
syrian troops planted their flag beside the american in the 
defense of saudi arabia on tuesday and arab harbormasters in the 
persian gulf kept embargoed iraqi freighters at bay turning up the 
heat in the simmering showdown with baghdad 
in washington the us and soviet superpowers conferred on 
putting a united nations umbrella over any antiiraq naval blockade 
the new middleman of the middle east jordans king hussein 
headed for the united states and a meeting with president bush 
carrying with him a private message from iraqs saddam hussein 
as peace efforts and economic pressure stepped up us military 
forces continued to pour across a 7000mile air bridge into the 
arabian desert it was the seventh day of desert shield the 
operation designed to face down an iraqi army that seized kuwait 
and could threaten saudi arabia 
out in the sand wastes paratroopers of the us armys 82nd 
airborne division found friendly saudis and some tastes of home 
like a delivery of fastfood burgers according to reports from 
journalists in a us media pool 
but the young americans also had to deal with 115degree heat 
and the potential for chemical warfare with iraq 
said one gi were trained and ready 
north across the desert hundreds of other americans remained 
trapped in kuwait and iraq 
one iraqi spokesman the ambassador to greece told reporters in 
athens the americans and thousands of other foreigners stranded 
when iraq invaded kuwait could leave as soon as the threats from 
the united states and its allies are eliminated 
the voice of america radio in a message beamed toward the 
troubled upper gulf cautioned the trapped americans an estimated 
2500 in kuwait and 500 to 600 in iraq not to try to flee across 
the kuwait border into saudi arabia due to the danger involved 
under all the pressure iraq sounded unyielding 
in baghdad the staterun newspaper aljumhuriya said iraq knows 
how to foil us measures if iraq is attacked it said iraq 
can move the battlefield to where the united states does not 
want or expect it to be 
iraq said it launched its lightning strike against kuwait aug 2 
because of disputes over oil and money it said kuwait deliberately 
cut iraqi oil revenues by overproducing its own oil and driving 
down prices and unfairly pressed for repayment of an estimated 15 
billion in kuwaiti loans to iraq the iraqis also cited old claims 
on kuwaiti territory 
after its conquest iraq announced the annexation of kuwait 
to underline that declaration the baghdad government this week 
began referring to kuwait city as a southern iraqi city 
at us urging the un security council on aug 6 ordered a 
worldwide punitive embargo on trade with iraq bush then dispatched 
us troops and warplanes to saudi arabia saying the massing of 
iraqi troops just across the border in kuwait threatened 
usaligned saudi arabia us oil supplies and ultimately the 
us economy on aug 10 twelve of 20 arab league nations voted to 
also send their troops to stand beside the saudis 
the latest arab contingent from syria began arriving in saudi 
arabia in the early morning tuesday said diplomatic sources in the 
saudi capital of riyadh no details were available on the size or 
kind of unit involved 
most of an estimated 5000 egyptian troops promised for the 
saudi defense were already there and moroccan troops are expected 
soon 
a total of at least 50000 us troops are expected to be 
committed to desert shield within weeks including marines army 
air assault forces paratroopers and infantry at times in recent 
days us air transports were landing every 10 minutes in saudi 
arabia with american soldiers and supplies 
facing them were an estimated 200000 iraqi troops in kuwait 
out in the warm aquamarine waters of the gulf meanwhile there 
was new evidence tuesday of the effectivness of the maritime 
embargo 
authorities in the united arab emirates refused permission for 
an iraqi freighter despite repeated appeals from the captain to 
enter the port of dubai the freighter alabid stood anchored 
uselessly three miles outside the dubai breakwater shipping 
sources said another iraqi freighter albaya also waited 
futilely off dubai the sources said 
the international embargo could cripple iraq by cutting off its 
allimportant trade exports of oil and imports of food and 
military supplies 
the sanctions are beginning to bite in baghdad said a yugoslav 
businessman who reached belgrade on tuesday we noticed that 
availability of foodstuffs has been reduced and sugar and 
flour are in short supply he said 
the bush administration has made clear that dozens of us navy 
ships assembling in the gulf region would be used to blockade iraqi 
maritime traffic if necessary but us allies and other un 
members object that the security council embargo resolution did not 
specifically authorize such a naval operation 
in an effort to reach an understanding the state department on 
tuesday summoned the washington ambassadors of the four other 
security council powers the soviet union britain france and 
china to discuss the possibility of establishing a joint un 
military command in the region or of flying the un flag on the 
warships in the gulf 
the soviets who have a handful of warships in the area have 
said they will not take part in a naval blockade except under 
security council auspices 
at un headquarters in new york diplomats said the security 
council was unlikely to act until after it hears reports friday on 
how the 159 un members are observing the embargo 
the boycott against iraq was far from solid particularly in 
neighboring jordan 
iraqbound cargo was still being landed at the jordanian port of 
aqaba off the red sea and eyewitnesses reported truck traffic 
continued normally across the iraqjordan border 
iraqs major oil outlets pipelines through turkey and saudi 
arabia were effectively shut down but a smaller line into jordan 
remained operating jordanian officials said and iraqi oil was 
being loaded into tanker trucks and sped to ships at aqaba 
