officials to seek ways to keep the animals off the road 
its a fairly severe problem particularly if its your car 
thats been hit said richard mccabe of the wildlife management 
institute in washington dc 
the problem is that with concentrated deer populations 
particularly in states like pennsylvania and northern wisconsin 
that are semimountainous you have highways that intersect travel 
