<TEXT>
if you ask albert sindlinger whether saddam 
hussein can provoke a recession in the united states he will 
respond how can he create a recession that is already nearly 
eight months old 
sindlingers staff measures economic strength or weakness by 
calling americans on the telephone every day every week in 
every state but alaska and hawaii to find out about their 
financial condition 
based on their detailed responses nearly 4300 of them for the 
month of july he determines if they have what he calls positive or 
negative household liquidity last month 687 percent of 
households reported negatively 
to sindlinger an octogenerian who has been making such calls 
for more than 30 years that evidence of recession is overwhelming 
conclusive beyond debate consumer activity he points out makes 
up most of gross national product 
government officials dont agree they say gnp is continuing to 
grow albeit by a tiny percentage and they have said so 
repeatedly they are likely to continue saying so until six 
straight months of shrinkage occur 
theyve manipulated the figures says sindlinger who vows 
later this month to demonstrate to corporate and financial clients 
how they did it all he will say for now is that it involved 
official revisions of gnp made july 27 
had they revised correctly he says gnp for the first and 
second quarters of 1990 would have shrunk by 02 percent and 03 
percent respectively instead of having risen according to the 
government by 17 percent and 12 percent 
to sindlinger nothing speaks more clearly about the economy 
than the pocketbooks of americas households they are the 
economys strength or weakness what happens to them happens 
collectively to the country 
calling from headquarters in wallingford pa sindlinger 
researchers ask heads of households these questions 
1 is your total combined household annual income now higher or 
the same as it was six months ago 
2 do you think your combined household annual income in the 
next six months will remain the same or be higher or lower than 
now 
3 do you believe that in the next six months there will be more 
or the same numbers of jobs where you work 
4 do you expect that business conditions in the next six months 
will be the same or better in your area 
if the respondent answers any of the four questions negatively 
the household is said to have negative household liquidity right 
now says sindlinger you can find negative liquidity in most of 
the country 
negative liquidity went beyond 50 percent of all households 
527 percent in january rose to nearly 80 percent in february and 
march dropped to 743 percent in april and has been just under 70 
percent since then 
based on interviewing through august 2 he lists 28 states as 
being clearly in recession with the most pronounced weakness being 
in new england the southeast southwest and the mideast or 
states of delaware maryland new jersey new york pennsylvania 
and the district of columbia 
the strongest states in the sindlinger accounting are illinois 
washington oregon ohio indiana minnesota utah and wisconsin a 
notch below them are iowa nevada colorado south dakota kansas 
montana and nebraska 
barely over the 50 percent line a critical demarcation in the 
sindlinger thesis are idaho missouri and michigan and sitting 
right on it are north dakota and wyoming the rest 28 of them 
have negative liquidity 
by sindlingers reckoning the recession began long before 
iraqs saddam hussein invaded kuwait even if it still isnt 
reflected in official government figures but it will be he says 
noting weakness in july retail sales 
he agrees that mideast troubles could worsen things but he will 
not he says make a projection without checking with his 
informants without listening to the voice of the people 
