don anderson was a student in london 
attending sessions of the house of commons when he could but 
thomas jefferson was on his mind 
what country can preserve its liberties jefferson wrote 
if their rulers are not warned from time to time that their 
people preserve the spirit of resistance 
rejuvenate democracy return power to the grassroots divide 
the counties into wards jefferson wrote 
in andersons mind jeffersons ideas became a resolution he 
would look for a way to apply them in the american south where he 
came from to empower poor blacks 
everybody said its impossible to organize an entire county or 
city the 58yearold anderson says now years later well 
thats exactly what weve done about 40 times 
the assemblies that he launched flourish in some places 
struggle in others but anderson keeps fanning the ember he might 
travel to a country church hall to explain his system or to a 
manhattan penthouse to mingle and seek donations 
anderson who grew up in a middleclass black family is a 
graduate of the london school of economics and the university of 
michigan and its law school he writes acts in shakespeare 
productions and plays the bagpipes 
but politics and economics have been his focus in 1964 as 
counsel to a us house subcommittee he helped draft the 
antipoverty economic opportunity act 
he concluded that alleviating poverty and not just its symptoms 
would require a selfhelp structure for whole communities so in 
1968 he founded the national association for the southern poor 
i left the marbled halls of the rayburn building he wrote 
for the remotest rural areas of virginia and north carolina to 
put the ideas of jefferson to work 
earlier this year andersons group received a plaque from the 
white house recognizing it as one of president bushs thousand 
points of light 
