perhaps for that reason that business has remained constant or 
improved in some cases despite the softening economy and rising 
travel costs 
people are accustomed to traveling and they like it said 
jerry cheskie spokesman for the american automobile association in 
heathrow fla theyre more apt to postpone the purchase of 
bigticket items like tvs or refrigerators than travel plans 
people will cut their trips short stay closer to home and forgo 
luxury accommodations but even fears of recession arent likely to 
keep them from hitting the open road this summer tourism officials 
said 
robert and florice cohagen plan to drive from their home in 
columbus ohio to houston to visit relatives 
wed rather not spend the extra money but it isnt going to 
stop us said cohagen 72it might only be worse next year 
thats the kind of attitude recommended by richard rippe chief 
economist at dean witter reynolds inc in new york 
we will face for a time somewhat higher inflation as the oil 
